19/02/2007
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) police chief Uros Pena said on Friday (February 16th) that intense activities are under way to detect and smash the network supporting top war crimes fugitives. 
Speaking after a meeting of the RS Interior Ministry's collegium in Banja Luka, Pena reiterated that according to current intelligence information, none of the indictees wanted by the UN war crimes tribunal is on RS territory.
In other news, RS chief special prosecutor Miodrag Bajic announced on Saturday that his department is investigating 18 suspicious privatisation cases. 
The probe was launched on the basis of information from the RS Commission for Revision of Privatisation Cases, including some related to the sale of state capital during the 1990s conflict. 
(Dnevni avaz - 18/02/07; Nezavisne novine, RTRS - 17/02/07; RTRS - 16/02/07)
